Today marks the seventh anniversary of Russia's invasion of Crimea, in which it violated international law and the sovereignty of Ukraine. The United States remains steadfast in its support for Ukraine and its allies. It does not recognize Russia's annexation of Crimea and will continue to stand against Russia's aggressive actions. The United States is committed to holding Russia accountable for its abuses and aggression in Ukraine. It also honors the courage and hope displayed by the Ukrainian people during the Revolution of Dignity, and supports efforts towards a peaceful, democratic, and prosperous future for Ukraine.